aws::graph::propositions: # Helicopter Accident During Air Taxi Maneuver
The helicopter was in normal operating conditions.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) applied aft cyclic to slow down.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) began air taxiing to the parking pad.
The parking pad was located to the east of their current position.
The parking pad was to the right of their current position.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) heard the low main rotor rpm audible horn.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) confirmed a loss of engine power.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) confirmed the loss of engine power by referencing indications in the cockpit.
The helicopter descended very rapidly toward the ground.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) surmised the engine was unable to produce power.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) reduced the collective briefly.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) reduced the collective to regain main rotor energy.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) applied collective to cushion the landing.
The helicopter impacted the runway.
The helicopter came to rest on its left side.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) reported it was unknown if the engine was still running after the helicopter came to rest.
The Pilot In Command (PIC) executed an emergency shutdown.
Both pilots egressed from the helicopter without further incident.
The helicopter sustained substantial damage to the main rotor system.
The helicopter sustained substantial damage to the fuselage.
The helicopter sustained substantial damage to the tailboom.
The helicopter sustained substantial damage to the tail rotor system.

text:
As the helicopter was in normal operating conditions, the PIC applied aft cyclic to slow down and began air taxiing to the parking pad to the east (right) of their current position. At that moment, he heard the low main rotor rpm audible horn. The PIC confirmed a loss of engine power by referencing indications in the cockpit. The helicopter descended very rapidly toward the ground and the PIC surmised the engine was unable to produce power. The PIC reduced the collective briefly to regain main rotor energy and then applied collective to cushion the landing. The helicopter impacted the runway and came to rest on its left side. The PIC reported it was unknown if the engine was stilling running after the helicopter came to rest. The PIC executed an emergency shutdown and both pilots egressed from the helicopter without further incident. The helicopter sustained substantial damage to the main rotor system, the fuselage, the tailboom, and the tail rotor system.
